        "## Exercise 2\n",
        "Next, we construct a universe of $N = 50$ synthetic assets following the single-factor model\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\tilde r_{i,t} = \\beta_i \\tilde r_{m,t} + \\varepsilon_{i,t}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "The factor loadings $\\beta_i$ and idiosyncratic volatilities $\\sigma_{\\varepsilon,i}$ are drawn from the distributions specified in the assignment. Using the estimated market moments from Exercise 1, we construct the true mean vector $\\mu$ and covariance matrix $\\Sigma$, which are treated as the true parameters throughout the remainder of the assignment."
      ],
      "id": "bc90214f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "cache": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: ex2-synthetic-assets\n",
        "\n",
        "N = 50\n",
        "\n",
        "beta = np.random.uniform(0.5, 1.5, N)\n",
        "sigma_epsilon = np.random.uniform(0.10 / np.sqrt(12), 0.30 / np.sqrt(12), N)\n",
        "\n",
        "mu = beta * mu_m\n",
        "Sigma = sigma2_m * np.outer(beta, beta) + np.diag(sigma_epsilon**2)"
      ],
      "id": "ex2-synthetic-assets",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
