        "## Exercise 5\n",
        "To study estimation error, we simulate asset returns from the true data-generating process and estimate the mean vector $\\hat{\\mu}$ and covariance matrix $\\hat{\\Sigma}$ from the simulated sample. These sample estimates are then used to construct a plug-in efficient frontier."
      ],
      "id": "4b255d92"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "cache": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: ex5-simulate-returns\n",
        "\n",
        "def simulate_returns(periods, expected_returns, covariance_matrix):\n",
        "    returns = np.random.multivariate_normal(\n",
        "        expected_returns,\n",
        "        covariance_matrix,\n",
        "        size=periods\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    return returns"
      ],
      "id": "ex5-simulate-returns",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "We first compare the true efficient frontier with the frontier estimated from a single simulated sample with $T = 120$ monthly observations."
      ],
      "id": "13585ec5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "cache": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: ex5-one-simulation\n",
        "\n",
        "T = 120\n",
        "\n",
        "simulated_returns = simulate_returns(T, mu, Sigma)\n",
        "\n",
        "mu_hat = simulated_returns.mean(axis=0)\n",
        "Sigma_hat = np.cov(simulated_returns, rowvar=False, ddof=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "frontier_hat = compute_efficient_frontier(mu_hat, Sigma_hat, n_points=100)\n",
        "tangency_hat = compute_tangency_portfolio(mu_hat, Sigma_hat)"
